      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HAPPY TOO YA (6) backs up after a good effort to finish only 3.7 metres away in fifth in a higher-graded race at Menangle on Saturday. Draws wide but is suited returning to a venue where he has won three of five attempts. ULTIMATE EMPIRE (7) is racing well having recorded two wins and two minor placings from five starts for this stable. Performed well once again when he came from a wide barrier for third at his latest appearance at Menangle. Should enjoy a nice smother from this draw and if he gets the gaps he is a winning hope. TOORAM CEE CEE (5) had a wide barrier in a tougher race at Menangle last start but placed from the second line at Newcastle prior and is proven at this circuit and distance. Last-start placegetter THERES WALLY (1) is up in grade and draws to be competitive again.",
